label("$x$", (44, 45));
label(scale(0.8)*"$10-x$",(28,58));
label(scale(0.8)*"$15-x$",(63,58));
[/asy]

Adding all four categories, we have  \[(10-x)+x+(15-x) + 8 = 30.\]Simplifying gives $33-x = 30$, so $x = \boxed{3}$.

We have \begin{align*}
2^{2001}\times5^{1950}\div4^{27}&= 2^{2001}\div2^{54}\times5^{1950} \\
&= 2^{1947}\times5^{1950}\\
&= (2\times5)^{1947}\times5^3 \\
&= 125\times10^{1947}
\end{align*}Since $125\times10^{1947}$ has three non-zero digits followed by 1947 zeros, it has a total of $\boxed{1950}$ digits.

