solution:
Let $OM = a$ and $ON = b$. Then $$
19^2 = (2a)^2 + b^2 \quad \text{and} \quad 22^2 = a^2 + (2b)^2.
$$ [asy]
unitsize(0.3cm);
pair X,Y,O,N,M;
X=(0,8);
O=(0,0);
Y=(13,0);
N=(6,0);
M=(0,4);
path a=X--Y--O--cycle;
path b=M--Y;
draw(a);
draw(X--N);
draw(shift((16,0))*a);
draw(shift((16,0))*b);
